   <mods:abstract>Pleased by his grandson's recent letter and happy to hear of his recovery
            frm illness. "Remember Him by whose kind Providence your Life has been preserved and be
            thankful." Urges him to pursue his Latin studies. Glad to hear the boy is pleased with
            his situation at school. "You are under the Care of a Preceptor, whom I have heard much
            commended." The whole family looks foward to his visit "the ensuing Season." Regards
            from his aunt and uncle. "While you continue my Dr Boy to behave and do well, you may
            rely on the Love of your affte. Grandfather."</mods:abstract>
